# Creating Minio Instance
This topic describes how to create Minio instances by developers.

## Create Minio instance on local storage

<%= image_tag("local-storage.png") %>

In this deployment, Minio will use VM's local persistent disk for storage. Use the following command to create a Minio instance:

```sh
cf create-service minio standard minio-instance-1 -c minio.conf
```

The minio.conf file should look like this:

```
{
  "accesskey": "randomaccesskey",
  "secretkey": "randomsecretkey"
}

```
Custom accesskey and secretkey should be provided.

## Start Minio with Azure Blob Storage backend

In this deployment, Minio will provide S3 API access for Azure Blob Storage.

<%= image_tag("azure.svg") %>

Run the following command to create Minio instance:

```sh
cf create-service minio standard minio-instance-1 -c minio.conf
```

The minio.conf file should look like this:

```
{
  "gateway": "azure",
  "accesskey": "azure-storage-account-name",
  "secretkey": "azure-storage-account-key"
}
```

Please change `azure-storage-account-name` and `azure-storage-account-key` with the actual Azure Account name and key.

## Create Minio for Google Cloud Storage backend

In this deployment, Minio will provide S3 API access for Google Cloud Storage.

<%= image_tag("gcs.svg") %>

```sh
cf create-service minio standard minio-instance-1 -c minio.conf
```

The minio.conf can be generated using [minio-cf](https://github.com/minio/minio-cf) command:

```sh
minio-cf --access-key randomaccesskey --secret-key randomsecretkey --gcs /path/to/credentials.json > minio.conf
```

Custom access-key and secret-key should be provided. Follow the steps in [this document](https://docs.minio.io/docs/minio-gateway-for-gcs) to generate the credentials.json file.

# Accessing Minio

## Minio Web-UI

After creating a Minio instance you can access the storage using Minio-WebUI. Get the Dashboard-URL using `cf service` command:

<%= image_tag("cf-service.png") %>

Access the Dashboard URL `https://d3ecc8f6-5684-4882-90c4-179285ff9b09.sys.your-pcf-domain.com` using Web-Browser

<%= image_tag("web-browser.png") %>

## Minio Client Tool

Install [mc](https://minio.io/downloads.html#download-client) and configure `mc` with the command:

```sh
mc config host add minio https://d3ecc8f6-5684-4882-90c4-179285ff9b09.sys.your-pcf-domain.com randomaccesskey randomsecretkey
```

Create Bucket:

```sh
mc mb minio/testbucket
```

Upload File:

```sh
mc cp /tmp/piano.mp3 minio/testbucket
```

Download File:

```sh
mc cp minio/testbucket/piano.mp3 /tmp/new-piano.mp3
```

Please check [documentation](https://docs.minio.io/docs/minio-client-complete-guide) for detailed usage of `mc`.

## Client SDKs

### Minio Client SDKs
Minio storage can be accessed through the following minio SDKs:

* [minio-go](https://docs.minio.io/docs/golang-client-quickstart-guide)
* [minio-java](https://docs.minio.io/docs/java-client-quickstart-guide)
* [minio-dotnet](https://docs.minio.io/docs/dotnet-client-quickstart-guide)
* [minio-js](https://docs.minio.io/docs/javascript-client-quickstart-guide)
* [minio-python](https://docs.minio.io/docs/python-client-quickstart-guide)

Sample Javascript code to upload a file using minio-js:

```js
var Minio = require('minio')

// Instantiate the minio client with the endpoint
// and access keys as shown below.
var minioClient = new Minio.Client({
    endPoint: 'd3ecc8f6-5684-4882-90c4-179285ff9b09.sys.your-pcf-domain.com',
    port: 443,
    secure: true,
    accessKey: 'randomaccesskey',
    secretKey: 'randomsecretkey'
});

// File that needs to be uploaded.
var file = '/tmp/photos-europe.tar'

// Make a bucket called europetrip.
minioClient.makeBucket('europetrip', '', function(err) {
    if (err) return console.log(err)

    // Using fPutObject API upload your file to the bucket europetrip.
    minioClient.fPutObject('europetrip', 'photos-europe.tar', file, 'application/octet-stream', function(err, etag) {
      if (err) return console.log(err)
      console.log('File uploaded successfully.')
    });
});
```

Please use the `accessKey` and `secretKey` that was used to create the Minio instance.

